{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01DeAByH9fwAk2BAquc3nbYS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the context needed. Here is the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go`\n\nAdd the `MaxImageInspectionRetries` field to `ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec`, after the `FallbackArchitecture` field (line 58):\n\n```go\n// ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec defines the desired state of ClusterPodPlacementConfig\ntype ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec struct {\n\t// LogVerbosity is the log level for the pod placement components.\n\t// Valid values are: \"Normal\", \"Debug\", \"Trace\", \"TraceAll\".\n\t// Defaults to \"Normal\".\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=Normal\n\tLogVerbosity common.LogVerbosityLevel `json:\"logVerbosity,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// NamespaceSelector selects the namespaces where the pod placement operand can process the nodeAffinity\n\t// of the pods. If left empty, all the namespaces are considered.\n\t// The default sample allows to exclude all the namespaces where the\n\t// label \"multiarch.openshift.io/exclude-pod-placement\" exists.\n\t// +optional\n\tNamespaceSelector *metav1.LabelSelector `json:\"namespaceSelector,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Plugins defines the configurable plugins for this component.\n\t// This field is optional and will be omitted from the output if not set.\n\t// +optional\n\tPlugins *plugins.Plugins `json:\"plugins,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// FallbackArchitecture defines the architecture to use if the image inspector cannot determine the image's architecture.\n\t// If configured, the PodPlacementController will set the node affinity of the pod to the fallback architecture\n\t// if the image inspector cannot determine the image's architecture.\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=\"\"\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=arm64;amd64;ppc64le;s390x;\"\"\n\tFallbackArchitecture string `json:\"fallbackArchitecture,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// MaxImageInspectionRetries is the maximum number of times the pod placement controller\n\t// will retry image inspection on transient errors before giving up and removing the scheduling gate.\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=5\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=20\n\tMaxImageInspectionRetries *int32 `json:\"maxImageInspectionRetries,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Exact change** — insert after line 58 (`FallbackArchitecture string ...`):\n\n```diff\n \tFallbackArchitecture string `json:\"fallbackArchitecture,omitempty\"`\n+\n+\t// MaxImageInspectionRetries is the maximum number of times the pod placement controller\n+\t// will retry image inspection on transient errors before giving up and removing the scheduling gate.\n+\t// +optional\n+\t// +kubebuilder:default=5\n+\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n+\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=20\n+\tMaxImageInspectionRetries *int32 `json:\"maxImageInspectionRetries,omitempty\"`\n }\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `api/v1alpha1/clusterPodPlacementConfig_conversion.go`\n\nAdd a new annotation constant and round-trip logic, following the same pattern as `FallbackArchAnnotation`. Add `\"strconv\"` to imports.\n\nFull updated file:\n\n```go\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\t\"strconv\"\n\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/conversion\"\n\n\tmultiarchv1beta1 \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/api/v1beta1\"\n)\n\nconst FallbackArchAnnotation = \"multiarch.openshift.io/fallback-architecture\"\nconst MaxImageInspectionRetriesAnnotation = \"multiarch.openshift.io/max-image-inspection-retries\"\n\n// ConvertTo converts this ClusterPodPlacementConfig to the Hub version v1beta1.\nfunc (src *ClusterPodPlacementConfig) ConvertTo(dstRaw conversion.Hub) error {\n\tdst := dstRaw.(*multiarchv1beta1.ClusterPodPlacementConfig)\n\n\t// ObjectMeta\n\tdst.ObjectMeta = src.ObjectMeta\n\n\t// Spec\n\tdst.Spec.LogVerbosity = src.Spec.LogVerbosity\n\tdst.Spec.Name